<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10123381>
    dc:description "Fig. 47. Scipopus (Phaeopterina) argentum sp. nov. A. Head, ♀, lateral view, Ecuador, non-type (USNM). B. Head and thorax, ♀, dorsal view, Ecuador, non-type (USNM). C. External male terminalia, lateral view, Ecuador, non-type (USNM). D. Internal male terminalia, lateral view, Ecuador, non-type (QCAZ). E. Female spermathecae and associated structures, Peru, non-type (USNM). F. Habitus, ♀, Peru, non-type (USNM). Abbreviations: b = basiphallus; bc = bursa copulatrix; bdp = basal distiphallus; e = epandrium; ea = ejaculatory apodeme; h = hypandrium; pb = phallic bulb; pd = paired spermathecal duct; ps = paired spermatheca; pss = paired spermathecal stems; sd = single spermathecal duct; sp = sperm pump; ss = single spermatheca." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10123381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

